  "summary": "ethers-io executes remote shell command from lifecycle script",
  "details": "The package name is a typosquat of the widely-used 'ethers' library. Its package.json lifecycle script invokes require('child_process') and execSync('curl...') during npm install, fetching and executing remote content on the installer's machine without user consent. This is the canonical install-time remote code execution pattern: a typosquat name used as a lure, combined with an install-time hook that runs an arbitrary shell command fetching attacker-controlled bytes. Any machine that runs `npm install ethers-io` hands code execution to the package publisher.",
